title: Aecom engineers space in Walker Corp tower
text:
The $2 billion Collins Square development at the western end of Collins Street is one of Melbourne's largest mixed-use commercial and retail developments. Photo: Arsineh Houspian
Global engineering group Aecom is the latest tenant to take space in billionaire Sydney property developer Lang Walker's Collins Square development.
Aecom will take three floors in Walker Corporation's Tower 2, the group confirmed, a total of 7000 square metres, as foreshadowed by BusinessDay in April.
The $2 billion Collins Square development at the western end of Collins Street is one of Melbourne's largest mixed-use commercial and retail developments.
The deal follows accounting firm KPMG signing a lease for nearly 30,000 square metres and legal firm Maddocks taking three floors in the 38-storey tower.
Walker Corporation was in discussions with other potential tenants to lease the remaining two floors.
It is also looking for anchor tenants for its fifth tower in the project, with contenders believed to include global financial services company Link Market Services, according to industry insiders.
The fifth and final 27-storey tower at 2-12 Batman Hill Drive was approved in February and will have a gross floor area of nearly 68,000 square metres.
